AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1630 House Bill No. 1497*
by adding the following as a new subsection (e) in Section 4:
(e) Notwithstanding subsection (a), a home rule municipality having a population
of not less than one hundred ninety thousand seven hundred (190,700) and not more
than one hundred ninety thousand eight hundred (190,800), according to the 2020 or a
subsequent federal census, may set the date of the municipal elections on such date as
prescribed in the municipality's charter.
